<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each block was meant to do something, but it is broken. Read what it is <strong>supposed</strong> to do, fix it on paper, then explain why the original was wrong.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — A correct answer should add <strong>one</strong> to the score. Right now the score never goes up, because the result of the addition is thrown away.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">score = 0
guess = &quot;table&quot;
answer = &quot;table&quot;
if guess == answer:
    score + 1
game.say(score)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> store the new total back into <code>score</code> with <code>score = score + 1</code>.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

